# Kabana Template Is the Design Source of Truth

For **any** storefront UI (templates, CSS, book cards, layouts, listings), follow the original static theme in `kabana/` — do **not** invent new layouts or “improve” the design from scratch.

The FastAPI app under `app/templates/` must reuse kabana’s structure and class names. Diverging from kabana caused broken grids, uneven covers, and truncated titles; matching kabana fixed it.

## Before changing UI

1. Open the matching page in `kabana/` (e.g. `kabana/categories.html`, `kabana/index.html`, `kabana/book-details.html`).
2. Copy its markup pattern and CSS classes into `app/templates/`.
3. Only then wire dynamic data (Jinja, book IDs, prices).

## Book cards & listings (required)

- Card markup must match kabana: `.properties.pb-30` → `.properties-card` → `.properties-img` + `.properties-caption.properties-caption2`.
- Shared card lives in `app/templates/macros.html` (`book_card`). Prefer that macro over one-off card HTML.
- Book grids (home, search, all books) must sit inside `.best-selling` (search/all-books: `.best-selling.p-0` like `kabana/categories.html`).
- Use kabana-style Bootstrap columns (e.g. `col-xxl-3 col-xl-3 col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6`).
- Do **not** apply slick-carousel margins (`.best-selling .properties { margin: 0 12px }`) to Bootstrap grid cards — those margins are for `.selling-active` only.

## Covers & titles

- Demo images in kabana are uniform; real covers are not. Keep equal cover boxes (`object-fit: cover`, fixed 2:3 area) without changing kabana’s card chrome.
- Missing covers → `/static/img/book/default.jpg` (and/or media proxy default). Never point `onerror` at a non-existent path.
- Titles: full card width (not a fixed ~150px). Prefer kabana caption styling + `1rem` title size on listings.

## Do / Don’t

```html
<!-- ✅ GOOD: matches kabana/categories.html -->
<div class="best-selling p-0">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xxl-3 col-xl-3 col-lg-4 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
      {{ book_card(book) }}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ❌ BAD: listing without .best-selling / custom card layout -->
<div class="listing-area">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="my-custom-card">...</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

- **Do** reuse kabana CSS from `app/static/css/style.css` and existing theme classes.
- **Don’t** redesign with new card systems, dashboards, or generic AI layouts when kabana already has the element.
- **Don’t** edit `kabana/` as the live app — treat it as the reference mock; implement in `app/templates/` + `app/static/`.
